<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880705-0099 </DOCNO><HL> Ten Firms Receive Contracts for Navy Air Force Equipment </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MD WX ML LOR UTX TXT GD GE </CO><IN> ARO </IN><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   General Electric Co. received defense contracts totaling $298 million for antisubmarine warfare combat systems for the Navy and aircraft engine improvements and weather satellite equipment for the Air Force.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. was awarded $118.4 million in contracts for FA-18 aircraft production, engineering services and training equipment for the Navy, and for airlift services for the Air Force.    Westinghouse Electric Corp. was issued Air Force contracts totaling $102.4 million for aircraft electronic equipment and radar services.    General Dynamics Corp. won $82.8 million in Navy contracts for submarine design services and missile test equipment.    Bell Helicopter Textron, a unit of Textron Inc., received a $27.5 million Navy contract for AH-1 helicopter modifications.    The Pratt andamp; Whitney unit of United Technologies Corp. was awarded a $24.6 million Navy contract for J52 aircraft engines.    Loral Corp. got a $21.6 million Navy contract for underwater mine equipment.    SLI Avionics Systems Corp. was issued a $19.7 million Air Force contract for development of a flight data recorder.    American Apparel Inc. won a $15.2 million Defense Logistics Agency contract for coats.    Martin Marietta Corp. received Air Force contracts totaling $13.3 million for space launch vehicle equipment and aircraft navigation and targeting equipment. </TEXT></DOC>